&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;class PostDetail(DetailView):
    model = Post


    def get_context_data(self, **kwargs):
        data = super(PostDetail, self).get_context_data(**kwargs)
        &lt;b&gt;self.object.view_count += 1&lt;/b&gt;
        self.object.save()
        return data&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

If you really want to protect this against race conditions, you can save the `view_count`, and then make a save with `F(&#39;view_count&#39;) + 1`:

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;class PostDetail(DetailView):
    model = Post


    def get_context_data(self, **kwargs):
        data = super(PostDetail, self).get_context_data(**kwargs)
        &lt;b&gt;vc = self.object.view_count&lt;/b&gt;
        self.object.view_count = F(&#39;view_count&#39;) + 1
        self.object.save()
        self.object.view_count = &lt;b&gt;vc + 1&lt;/b&gt;
        return data&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

